Recent changes: Added neighbor counting with Set-based lookup and survival rule (keep cells with 2 or 3 neighbors). Only filters existing live cells, no birth logic yet.

Current implementation:
```typescript
export const nextGeneration = (grid: number[][]): number[][] => {
  const alive = new Set(grid.map(([x, y]) => `${x},${y}`));
  return grid.filter(([x, y]) => {
    let count = 0;
    for (let dx = -1; dx <= 1; dx++) {
      for (let dy = -1; dy <= 1; dy++) {
        if (dx === 0 && dy === 0) continue;
        if (alive.has(`${x + dx},${y + dy}`)) count++;
      }
    }
    return count === 2 || count === 3;
  });
};
```

